        "body": "Resolves #1622\n\n## Summary\n\n- Preserve the shared Cursor team on-demand pool as the headline budget.\n- Carry the current member's individual on-demand spend alongside that pool.\n- Render a localized `Your spend` row only when personal spend is positive.\n- Include row presence in layout compatibility and height fingerprints.\n\n## Proof\n\n- `swift test --filter Cursor`: 52 tests passed across 5 suites.\n- Covers team pool + personal spend, personal-budget behavior, zero-spend omission, row rendering, and height-fingerprint invalidation.\n- `make check`: passed; SwiftLint found 0 violations in 1,144 files.\n- Maintainer lint repair review: clean, confidence 0.78.\n- Full branch autoreview: clean, confidence 0.82.\n- `git diff --check`: passed.\n\n## Visual proof\n\n- Deterministic 320 px real-view screenshot from the reviewed implementation showed the personal-spend card without clipping.\n- This rebase only moved the compatibility initializer from `MenuCardView.swift` to the existing costs extension to stay under the file-length limit; rendering behavior is unchanged.\n- Exact live Cursor account proof remains blocked by protected Chrome Safe Storage login-Keychain authorization; no credential or privacy setting was changed.\n\n## Review\n\n- Rebased onto current `main`.\n- Preserved all 21 app translations and contributor changelog credit.\n- Fixed the post-rebase SwiftLint file-length violation without changing behavior.\n",
